        <metamark function="pagenumber"><num><hi rend="circled">78</hi></num></metamark>
        <p>
          so hideous as <hi rend="u">He</hi>... I had gazed on him<lb/>
          while unfinished; <del type="crossedOut" hand="#MWS" rend="black ink">and I thought</del> he<lb/>
          was ugly then. But when those muscles<lb/>
          and joints were endued with motion<lb/>
          it became a thing <del type="crossedOut" hand="#MWS" rend="black ink">to</del> such as even Dante<lb/>
          could never have conceived.<lb/>
        </p>
        <p>
          I passed the night wretchedly–<lb/>
          sometimes my pulses beat so quickly and<lb/>
          ha<add place="supralinear" hand="#MWS" rend="black ink">r</add><metamark>&#8248;</metamark><note>'^' is used as a metamark to indicate where 'r' should be inserted</note>dly that I felt the palpitation of<lb/>
          every artery: At others I nearly sunk<lb/>
          to the ground <del type="crossedOut" hand="#PBS" rend="black ink">with</del><add place="supralinear">thro</add> languor and ex-<lb/>
          treme weakness. <del type="crossedOut" hand="#MWS" rend="black ink">Surely so wretched a</del><lb/>
          <add place="marginleft" hand="#MWS" rend="black ink"><metamark>X</metamark><note>'X' is used as a metamark, presumably to indicate where the text in the left margin belongs</note><lb/>
          and mingled<lb/>
          with this hor<lb/>
          ror I felt the<lb/>
          bitterness of<lb/>
          <del type="crossedOut" hand="MWS" rend="black ink">disapp</del><lb/>
          disappoint<lb/>
          ment:<lb/></add>
          <metamark>X</metamark><note>'X' is used as a metamark, presumably to indicate where the text in the margin left belongs</note><del type="crossedOut" hand="#MWS" rend="black ink">creature as I never before existed.</del><lb/>
          Dreams that had been my food and<lb/>
          rest for so long a space were now<lb/>
          become a hell to me– <del type="crossedOut" hand="#MWS" rend="black ink">I</del> and the<lb/>
          change was so rapid, the overthrow<lb/>
          so complete.<lb/>
        </p>
        <p>
          Morning — dismal and wet — at leng <del type="overwritten" hand="#MWS" rend="black ink">ht</del>th<lb/>
          dawned, and <del type="crossedOut" hand="#MWS" rend="black ink">to</del> discovered to my sleepless<lb/>
          and aching eyes the <unclear>church</unclear><note>Unclear because of ink blots</note> of Ingols-<lb/>
          stadt its white steeple &amp; <del type="crossedOut" hand="#PBS" rend="black ink"><add place="supralinear" hand="#PBS" rend="black ink">the</add></del> <add place="supralinear" hand="#PBS" rend="black ink">its</add>clock which<lb/>
          pointed to the sixth<del type="crossedOut" hand="#MWS" rend="black ink">e</del> hour. The porter<lb/>
          opened the gates of the court which had<lb/>
          that night been my assylum and I<lb/>
          issued into the streets, pacing <add place="supralinear" hand="#PBS" rend="black ink">them</add> with<lb/>
          quick steps as if I <del type="crossedOut" hand="#MWS" rend="black ink">ough</del> sought to<lb/>
          <add place="marginleft" hand="#PBS" rend="black ink">avoid</add>the wretch whom I feared every turn-<lb/>
          ing in the street would present to<lb/>
